      • getAcctWithBankIdentifier

        public TField getAcctWithBankIdentifier()
        Returns the AcctWithBankIdentifier

        Field description: This field will hold the 5 letter ISO identifier Example : GBDSC. When payment is sent to TPH, this will be stored in field CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID.CODE in table POR.SUPPLIMENTARY.INFO System uses this code, looks up the table ISO.CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID and fetches the 2 letter SWIFT prefix from field SWIFT.PREFIX. System concatenates '//' followed by the extracted swift prefix followed by the value in ACCT.BANK.CLEARING.CODE. This concatenated value is also sent to TPH and stored in field PARTY.ACCOUNT.LINE in POR.SUPPLIMENTARY.INFO (For role ACWINS). Example : If Swift Prefix for GBDSC is SC and ACCOUNT.WITH.BANK.CLEARING.CODE contains 4352, value formed would be //SC4352

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The AcctWithBankIdentifier

      • getOrderingPaymentFxCustRate

        public TField getOrderingPaymentFxCustRate()
        Returns the OrderingPaymentFxCustRate

        Field description: Customer rate for the conversion between payment currency and ordering currency Validation Rules: Allowed only when ALLOW.FX.RATE is set to YES in PAYMENT.ORDER.PRODUCT Customer rate needs to be equal to the sum of FX spread and Treasury rate When all the 3 fields -Cust rate, Spread and Treasury are- are input, get the default treasury rate for the currency pair from Currency application. If the user input treasury rate is equal to the default treasury rate, calculate the spread, and repopulate,if required When only Customer rate is input, treasury rate and spread are calculated and populated into the application. Override is raised if the spread is negative Override is raised if the rate tolerance percentage exceeds that of the value maintained in the PO Product Not all the 3 fields can be changed during amendment

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The OrderingPaymentFxCustRate

      • getOrderingPaymentFxSpread

        public TField getOrderingPaymentFxSpread()
        Returns the OrderingPaymentFxSpread

        Field description: Customer spread for the conversion between payment currency and ordering currency Validation Rules: Allowed only when ALLOW.FX.RATE is set to YES in PAYMENT.ORDER.PRODUCT FX spread is added to the treasury rate to calculate the Cust rate When FX spread and treasury rates are input, Cust rate is calculated and populated back to the PO record. When only FX spread is input, both Cust rate and treasury rate are arrived at and populated back to the PO record. When Cust rate and FX spread are input, spread is calculated again and populated into the PO record. Treasury rate is calculated as well. Override is raised if the rate tolerance percentage exceeds that of the value maintained in the PO Product Not all the 3 fields can be changed during amendment

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The OrderingPaymentFxSpread

      • getOrderingPaymentTreasuryRate

        public TField getOrderingPaymentTreasuryRate()
        Returns the OrderingPaymentTreasuryRate

        Field description: Treasury rate for the conversion between payment currency and ordering currency Validation Rules: Allowed only when ALLOW.FX.RATE is set to YES in PAYMENT.ORDER.PRODUCT When only treasury rate is input, both Cust rate and FX spread are calculated and defaulted into the PO application. When Cust rate and treasury rates are input, both spread and treasury rates are calculated. Override is raised if the spread is negative Override is raised if the rate tolerance percentage exceeds that of the value maintained in the PO Product

        Parameters:
        Returns:
        TField - The OrderingPaymentTreasuryRate

      • setAcctWithBankIdentifier

        public void setAcctWithBankIdentifier(TField value)
        Set the specified value for AcctWithBankIdentifier
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field will hold the 5 letter ISO identifier Example : GBDSC. When payment is sent to TPH, this will be stored in field CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID.CODE in table POR.SUPPLIMENTARY.INFO System uses this code, looks up the table ISO.CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID and fetches the 2 letter SWIFT prefix from field SWIFT.PREFIX. System concatenates '//' followed by the extracted swift prefix followed by the value in ACCT.BANK.CLEARING.CODE. This concatenated value is also sent to TPH and stored in field PARTY.ACCOUNT.LINE in POR.SUPPLIMENTARY.INFO (For role ACWINS). Example : If Swift Prefix for GBDSC is SC and ACCOUNT.WITH.BANK.CLEARING.CODE contains 4352, value formed would be //SC4352

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

        Field description: This field will hold the 5 letter ISO identifier Example : GBDSC. Sytsem uses this code, looks up the table ISO.CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID and fetches the 2 letter SWIFT prefix from field SWIFT.PREFIX. Sytem concatenates '//' followed by the extracted swift prefix followed by the value in BEN.BANK.CLEARING.CODE. This concatenated value is also sent to TPH and stored in field PARTY.ACCOUNT.LINE in POR.SUPPLIMENTARY.INFO (For role BENFCY). Example : If Swift Prefix for GBDSC is SC and BEN.BANK.CLEARING.CODE contains 4352, value formed would be //SC4352

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setBenIdentifier

        public void setBenIdentifier(TField value)
        Set the specified value for BenIdentifier
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: This field will hold the 5 letter ISO identifier Example : GBDSC. When payment is sent to TPH, this will be stored in field CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID.CODE in table POR.SUPPLIMENTARY.INFO. Sytsem uses this code, looks up the table ISO.CLEARING.SYSTEM.ID and fetches the 2 letter SWIFT prefix from field SWIFT.PREFIX.       • setOrderingPaymentFxCustRate

        public void setOrderingPaymentFxCustRate(TField value)
        Set the specified value for OrderingPaymentFxCustRate
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Customer rate for the conversion between payment currency and ordering currency Validation Rules: Allowed only when ALLOW.FX.RATE is set to YES in PAYMENT.ORDER.PRODUCT Customer rate needs to be equal to the sum of FX spread and Treasury rate When all the 3 fields -Cust rate, Spread and Treasury are- are input, get the default treasury rate for the currency pair from Currency application. If the user input treasury rate is equal to the default treasury rate, calculate the spread, and repopulate,if required When only Customer rate is input, treasury rate and spread are calculated and populated into the application. Override is raised if the spread is negative Override is raised if the rate tolerance percentage exceeds that of the value maintained in the PO Product Not all the 3 fields can be changed during amendment

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing

      • setOrderingPaymentFxSpread

        public void setOrderingPaymentFxSpread(TField value)
        Set the specified value for OrderingPaymentFxSpread
        Throws an UnsupportedOperationException if the object is not modifiable.

        Field description: Customer spread for the conversion between payment currency and ordering currency Validation Rules: Allowed only when ALLOW.FX.RATE is set to YES in PAYMENT.ORDER.PRODUCT FX spread is added to the treasury rate to calculate the Cust rate When FX spread and treasury rates are input, Cust rate is calculated and populated back to the PO record. When only FX spread is input, both Cust rate and treasury rate are arrived at and populated back to the PO record. When Cust rate and FX spread are input, spread is calculated again and populated into the PO record. Treasury rate is calculated as well. Override is raised if the rate tolerance percentage exceeds that of the value maintained in the PO Product Not all the 3 fields can be changed during amendment

        Parameters:
        value - The value to set
        Returns:
        nothing
